               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1913" notAfter="1916">The date of book one (<locus from="1r" to="103v"/>) is somewhere in the range of 1913–1916, during the reign of Iyasu (V, 1913–16, <locus target="#31v"/>), King Mǝnilǝk (1889–1913, <locus target="#85r #85v"/>) is also mentioned, as are Archbishop Peṭros (IV, 1881–1921, <locus target="#53v"/>), Abba Yoḥannəs (<locus target="#53v #55r"/> [unclear, possibly referring to the name of Archbishop Peṭros IV before taking his official title]), and Bishop Marqos (unknown, <locus target="#55r"/>).</origDate>
                     <origDate notBefore="1889" notAfter="1913">The date of book two (<locus from="104r" to="236v"/>) is 1889–1913, during the reign of King Mǝnilǝk (1889–1913, <locus target="#85r #85v #207v"/>), with the mention of Archbishop Peṭros (IV, 1881–1921, <locus target="#53v #207r"/>), and Metropolitan Qerǝlos (Cyril V, 1875–1927, <locus target="#204r #207r"/>).</origDate>
